    {
      "number": 19,
      "id": "I_kwDOOAZd1M6yoOgu",
      "title": "Select by signer as well",
      "url": "https://github.com/rats-endorsements-distribution/draft-howard-rats-coserv/issues/19",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "deeglaze",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "A reference value provider (e.g., Firmware vendor) can provide measurements for an environment whose name it does not own (e.g., Silicon vendor-named bootloader target). If I want to get reference values for the bootloader target that are specifically from a particular signer, then CoSERV does not allow me to name that.\n\nIf I select by manifest-signer role in the entity map, then since that's optional for directly signed CoRIMs in favor of the mandatory corim-meta  COSE header, then you'd need to search that as well. We don't even have a required structure for the manifest-signer, so I've opened https://github.com/ietf-rats-wg/draft-ietf-rats-corim/issues/421",
      "createdAt": "2025-04-15T15:49:12Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-04-15T15:49:12Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 21,
      "id": "I_kwDOOAZd1M6zcvn5",
      "title": "Consider \"audit bundle\" payloads in responses",
      "url": "https://github.com/rats-endorsements-distribution/draft-howard-rats-coserv/issues/21",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "paulhowardarm",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "In earlier discussions around Endorsement API endpoints, we theorised two trust models:\n\n- The \"shallow\" trust model, where the endorsement service alone is trusted to aggregate and convey on behalf of the whole supply chain.\n- The \"deep\" trust model, where the client trusts the endorsement service in the first instance, but may also need access to the original resources that were aggregated from primary supply chain entities.\n\nCoSERV as currently written caters quite well for the shallow model, but we need to think about how it could adopt the deep model (even if our PoC activities exclude that model for now).\n\n",
      "createdAt": "2025-04-22T10:29:35Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-04-22T10:29:35Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    }
