    {
      "number": 13,
      "id": "PR_kwDOOAZd1M6Rmkrp",
      "title": "Restructure the draft to latest CDDL",
      "url": "https://github.com/rats-endorsements-distribution/draft-howard-rats-coserv/pull/13",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "paulhowardarm",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "A round of extensions and refactoring to match the draft prose to the CDDL data model.\r\n\r\n- Introduction is rewritten to expand the scope of CoSERV to include both queries _and_ result sets.\r\n- A new top-level \"Information Model\" section is introduced, so that we can keep informational concepts and structure distinct from the precise data model.\r\n- Top-level \"CoSERV Query Language\" heading changed to \"Data Model\"\r\n- CDDL section refactored to reflect the new top-level wrapper object, with the query now nested within it.\r\n\r\nThis is just a minimal set to make the prose more honest with respect to the CDDL. After this, we can probably do more refactoring to lift some verbosity out of the data model and put it into the information model instead.\r\n\r\nSigned-off-by: Paul Howard <paul.howard@arm.com>",
      "createdAt": "2025-04-07T09:53:46Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-04-07T16:36:38Z",
      "baseRepository": "rats-endorsements-distribution/draft-howard-rats-coserv",
      "baseRefName": "main",
      "baseRefOid": "470f2ff59889e2f4518235f33122cfec6a9f9948",
