    {
      "number": 23,
      "id": "PR_kwDOOAZd1M6T7Y0H",
      "title": "[EXP] add authority to the result triples",
      "url": "https://github.com/rats-endorsements-distribution/draft-howard-rats-coserv/pull/23",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "thomas-fossati",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "First stab at adding explicit authority to result triples.\r\n\r\nThe idea explored in this PR is to wrap the existing triples in a map, which contains the authority context as \"crypto-key.\u201d\r\n\r\nThe downside of this approach is that it could potentially become extremely redundant, especially if the crypto-key is a cert or a cert chain.\r\n\r\nPossible mitigations include using \"CBOR packed\u201d or creating an auxiliary dictionary.",
      "createdAt": "2025-04-25T15:00:05Z",
